Class TreeNode2

  • java.lang.Object
    • TreeNode2

  • public class TreeNode2
extends Object
    TreeNode2 along with Tree2 is intended to be an object-oriented conversion of the tnode struct and functions in K&R pp. 140-142.

    • Method Detail

      • addTree

        public void addTree(String w)
        addtree adds (or modifies) a node for a word w into the tree/subtree headed by this node. If the word is already in this tree, only the count is incremented; no new node is created.

        This needs to take care of null differently because methods can't be called on null.

        Parameters:
        w - the word to be added into the tree

      • treePrint

        public void treePrint()
        treePrint prints the tree/subtree headed by this node in-order on standard output.

        This needs to take care of null differently because methods can't be called on null.
